================================================================================
Third-party software
================================================================================

MyAgent bundles and depends on third-party open-source packages, each under its
own license. The dependency tree is overwhelmingly permissive (MIT, BSD,
Apache-2.0, ISC). Notable items:

  - Electron, xterm.js, CodeMirror, lit, better-sqlite3, onnxruntime-web,
    @huggingface/transformers, pdfkit, and others — MIT / BSD / Apache-2.0 / ISC.

  - @img/sharp (transitive) — Apache-2.0 AND LGPL-3.0-or-later. Used as an
    unmodified, dynamically-linked npm dependency; its license text is retained
    in node_modules and redistributed with any distribution that includes it.

For the complete, authoritative list of dependency licenses, generate it from
the lockfile, e.g.:

    npx license-checker --production --json

